1. The BMIs in groups A and B were significantly higher than group C.
2. The significance level of the BMI difference between group A and group C is less than 0.001.
3. The significance level of the BMI difference between group B and group C is less than 0.01.
4. The BMI differences between group A and group B were not statistically significant.
5. The significance level of the BMI difference between group A and group B is greater than 0.05.
